they were treated to a KIDS CONE.

@Steve Daniel - Are you sure? 

Do you own a dictionary? If not, there are lots of online dictionaries you could consult. 

You could also read the comments already posted by people who think that "UPSA" is correct.

@Michelle 

I'm with you to the NTH degree! 

I often think that very thing, myself, and often can't resist reading some of the most indignant comments to my husband, who doesn't do the puzzle but who does enjoy my indignation about other people's indignation. Ha!

@lrubin 

Letter substitution themes are very common among the NYT puzzles.  Though perhaps not groundbreaking as a concept, this theme is about as normal as they come.

The point of a crossword puzzle is ALWAYS to guess what the constructor--or editor--was thinking.
